39
00:01:58,243 --> 00:01:59,242
Excuse me.

40
00:01:59,735 --> 00:02:02,258
Where's Humpty Javelin?
Does he work here?

41
00:02:02,543 --> 00:02:06,246
Uh, Humpty works the carousel, uh,
but today he's working nights.

42
00:02:06,791 --> 00:02:08,088
Do you know where he lives?

43
00:02:08,549 --> 00:02:10,908
Uh...it's around here.

44
00:02:11,392 --> 00:02:12,544
You can ask Ginny.

45
00:02:12,896 --> 00:02:13,810
Ginny?

46
00:02:13,927 --> 00:02:15,513
Yeah, h-his wife.

47
00:02:15,756 --> 00:02:18,341
Um, she works at
Ruby's Clam House.

48
00:02:18,482 --> 00:02:20,873
Just keep going down
that way there.

49
00:02:21,788 --> 00:02:22,804
Thank you.

50
00:02:22,883 --> 00:02:24,289
Yeah. You have a good one.

51
00:03:02,226 --> 00:03:04,945
Excuse me, do you
know if Ginny's here?

52
00:03:05,084 --> 00:03:06,397
Yeah. I'm Ginny.

53
00:03:06,648 --> 00:03:07,859
I'm Carolina.

54
00:03:08,140 --> 00:03:08,976
Who?

55
00:03:09,218 --> 00:03:11,179
Carolina. Humpty's daughter.

56
00:03:16,577 --> 00:03:17,632
Jesus.

57
00:03:20,229 --> 00:03:22,057
Is he gonna be surprised.

58
00:03:22,510 --> 00:03:24,080
I know he's gonna be upset.

59
00:03:24,572 --> 00:03:26,002
But I had to come here.

60
00:03:26,196 --> 00:03:28,821
I didn't want to but I...
don't have a choice.

61
00:03:31,892 --> 00:03:33,619
I'll tell you the truth.

62
00:03:35,736 --> 00:03:38,056
I don't think
he ever expected this.

63
00:03:39,229 --> 00:03:40,424
You're his wife?

64
00:03:41,479 --> 00:03:43,049
Why are you looking at me?

65
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:46,252
You're much younger
than I would've imagined.

66
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:48,182
Really?

67
00:03:49,612 --> 00:03:51,213
I don't feel much younger.

68
00:03:52,546 --> 00:03:54,085
I was thinking of my mother.

69
00:03:54,210 --> 00:03:56,139
When she died,
she was practically

70
00:03:56,256 --> 00:03:57,639
all gray.

71
00:03:58,389 --> 00:03:59,600
I look like her.

72
00:04:00,808 --> 00:04:02,948
Humpty should be back
in half an hour.

73
00:04:03,675 --> 00:04:06,308
He went fishing off the
pier at Sheepshead Bay.

74
00:04:06,542 --> 00:04:08,706
I'd always heard that
he'd moved to New Jersey.

75
00:04:09,081 --> 00:04:11,808
No, we got run out
of our place there.

76
00:04:11,909 --> 00:04:12,722
Oh.

77
00:04:12,761 --> 00:04:15,198
Well, I'm not telling you
anything new about your father.

78
00:04:15,956 --> 00:04:18,401
He fell off the wagon and
busted up the lobby.

79
00:04:20,497 --> 00:04:21,216
Oh.

80
00:04:22,318 --> 00:04:24,333
I guess you're
used to all this noise.

81
00:04:24,904 --> 00:04:26,302
You never get used to it.

82
00:04:27,013 --> 00:04:28,075
I hate it.

83
00:04:28,318 --> 00:04:30,271
This whole honky-tonk fairyland.

84
00:04:32,169 --> 00:04:33,404
We live up here.

85
00:04:48,616 --> 00:04:50,491
The place used to house
a freak show.

86
00:04:51,903 --> 00:04:53,505
We had to do
a lot of fixing up.

87
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:55,192
Oh, God.

88
00:04:55,653 --> 00:04:58,254
I hope when sees me
he doesn't fly off the handle.

89
00:04:58,279 --> 00:05:00,302
-No, I don't think--
-I hope he doesn't throw me out.

90
00:05:00,327 --> 00:05:01,934
I-I don't know what I'll do.

91
00:05:02,099 --> 00:05:03,380
I don't have
a dime to my name.

92
00:05:03,405 --> 00:05:05,451
I literally don't have
ten pennies.

93
00:05:09,446 --> 00:05:13,079
This-this-this goddamn noise!
I tell you.

94
00:05:13,243 --> 00:05:14,728
You never get used to it.

95
00:05:14,797 --> 00:05:16,470
Oh, my head's throbbing.

96
00:05:16,782 --> 00:05:18,126
And my--my kid--

97
00:05:18,211 --> 00:05:20,367
My kid had some trouble
in school today.

98
00:05:20,424 --> 00:05:21,603
You and my father
have a child?

99
00:05:21,673 --> 00:05:23,586
No, from my first husband.

100
00:05:23,681 --> 00:05:25,110
Don't ever have kids.

101
00:05:25,392 --> 00:05:27,712
Oh. Now my head's
cracking open.

102
00:05:27,938 --> 00:05:29,603
I get migraines.

103
00:05:30,954 --> 00:05:33,384
If you don't like Coney Island,
why don't you move?

104
00:05:37,398 --> 00:05:39,156
From your mouth to God's ears.

105
00:05:41,531 --> 00:05:42,578
Money, honey.

106
00:05:43,695 --> 00:05:46,195
Mazuma, the wherewithal.

107
00:05:47,039 --> 00:05:47,921
Ginny!

108
00:05:48,437 --> 00:05:49,710
Ginny, big score.

109
00:05:50,507 --> 00:05:51,289
Fluke,

110
00:05:51,562 --> 00:05:52,656
flounder,

111
00:05:53,343 --> 00:05:54,905
some uh, blue claws.

112
00:06:00,442 --> 00:06:01,254
No.

113
00:06:03,691 --> 00:06:05,465
No, what the hell
you doin' here?

114
00:06:06,443 --> 00:06:09,045
I told you never to step
foot in my home again.

115
00:06:09,850 --> 00:06:12,186
I'm in serious trouble,
I couldn't help it.

116
00:06:14,068 --> 00:06:15,310
You let her in in here?

117
00:06:16,998 --> 00:06:18,271
Christ!

118
00:06:21,698 --> 00:06:22,823
I don't believe this.

119
00:06:26,543 --> 00:06:28,214
You needs to go. Come on.

120
00:06:28,314 --> 00:06:29,433
-Go.
-I can't.

121
00:06:30,071 --> 00:06:31,540
If they fine me,
they're gonna kill me.

122
00:06:31,568 --> 00:06:32,140
You--

123
00:06:32,165 --> 00:06:33,915
You better hear her out, Humpty.

124
00:06:33,988 --> 00:06:35,283
Mind your own business.

125
00:06:35,308 --> 00:06:36,683
I got a bad headache!

126
00:06:36,715 --> 00:06:39,113
And Richie did it again,
you were supposed to talk to him.

127
00:06:39,191 --> 00:06:40,284
I talked to him.

128
00:06:40,332 --> 00:06:41,636
Frank's gonna kill me.

129
00:06:42,550 --> 00:06:43,573
I ran away and

130
00:06:43,792 --> 00:06:45,525
I took nothing,
I-I have no clothes,

131
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:47,230
I've been sleeping
in the rain.

132
00:06:48,414 --> 00:06:49,609
And I'm marked.

133
00:06:50,375 --> 00:06:51,336
They're gonna kill me.

134
00:06:51,742 --> 00:06:54,156
Well, that's what you get
when you marry a gangster.

135
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:56,343
Jesus, they're not gonna
come after you here, are they?

136
00:06:56,444 --> 00:06:57,585
I don't want trouble.

137
00:06:57,874 --> 00:06:59,351
Do you hear what I'm saying?

138
00:06:59,687 --> 00:07:01,015
They're gonna kill me.

139
00:07:01,062 --> 00:07:02,383
There's a young kid here!

140
00:07:02,475 --> 00:07:03,531
This is not our problem.

141
00:07:03,556 --> 00:07:05,773
All right, all right,
all right, knock it off.

142
00:07:07,172 --> 00:07:08,680
I-I gotta have a drink.

143
00:07:08,766 --> 00:07:10,078
No, Humpty, you've been good.

144
00:07:10,103 --> 00:07:12,789
I g--I.. I.. I need one.

145
00:07:12,845 --> 00:07:14,570
I need one,
look what's goin' on here!

146
00:07:14,595 --> 00:07:15,775
No booze!

147
00:07:16,165 --> 00:07:17,633
I'll make you coffee.

148
00:07:18,822 --> 00:07:20,798
Goddammit.

149
00:07:20,843 --> 00:07:22,217
What the hell do you
expect to happen

150
00:07:22,242 --> 00:07:23,991
when you marry
a cheap hoodlum?

151
00:07:24,420 --> 00:07:25,787
I was twenty.

152
00:07:26,108 --> 00:07:27,373
I didn't know better.

153
00:07:28,242 --> 00:07:29,304
I'm sorry.

154
00:07:29,609 --> 00:07:31,124
Why didn't you
go to the police?

155
00:07:31,226 --> 00:07:33,632
I told the police too much,
that's the problem.

156
00:07:34,078 --> 00:07:35,492
Why the hell
you open your mouth?

157
00:07:35,734 --> 00:07:37,242
The police told me
that I could be looking at

158
00:07:37,267 --> 00:07:39,281
five years
if I didn't cooperate.

159
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:41,374
What the hell do you know?

160
00:07:41,545 --> 00:07:44,295
Since when do you know what
happens inside the rackets?

161
00:07:44,806 --> 00:07:46,017
How could I not know?

162
00:07:46,657 --> 00:07:48,115
Can't be married
to one of those guys

163
00:07:48,204 --> 00:07:50,079
and not pick up
on what's going on.

164
00:07:51,959 --> 00:07:53,443
Jesus Christ!

165
00:07:54,006 --> 00:07:56,365
I told you not
to marry that racketeer!

166
00:07:56,427 --> 00:07:58,177
I told you he was all mobbed up.

167
00:07:58,279 --> 00:07:59,685
He stank of murder.

168
00:08:00,811 --> 00:08:03,967
She found this-this
greaseball exciting.

169
00:08:04,498 --> 00:08:06,545
He wasn't even good-lookin'!

170
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:08,977
He was a punk.

171
00:08:11,984 --> 00:08:13,243
I need a drink!

172
00:08:13,297 --> 00:08:14,243
Forget it, Humpty.

173
00:08:14,344 --> 00:08:16,602
I need one, goddammit!

174
00:08:17,215 --> 00:08:18,715
Calm down.

175
00:08:28,772 --> 00:08:30,608
Jesus Christ.

176
00:08:32,050 --> 00:08:34,667
God damn it, she could've
married a few guys

177
00:08:34,692 --> 00:08:36,910
from school, from
the neighborhood, all of 'em.

178
00:08:37,051 --> 00:08:38,348
Decent kids.

179
00:08:40,051 --> 00:08:41,653
We raised her nice.

180
00:08:42,342 --> 00:08:43,545
Your mother and I

181
00:08:43,731 --> 00:08:46,044
we broke our backs
out of workin'

182
00:08:46,092 --> 00:08:47,779
so you could go to college

183
00:08:47,820 --> 00:08:49,569
and-and you know,
you didn't.

184
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:52,743
You threw it all away!

185
00:08:53,844 --> 00:08:56,469
Look at ya--
you're such a beautiful girl!

186
00:08:58,352 --> 00:08:59,493
You had your pick.

187
00:09:00,079 --> 00:09:01,985
I loved Frank, okay?

188
00:09:02,626 --> 00:09:04,954
And all the guys you
hand-picked for me, they were--

189
00:09:05,219 --> 00:09:07,665
dull, colorless, boring guys.

190
00:09:07,782 --> 00:09:10,680
All of 'em, honest men,
every one of 'em.

191
00:09:12,516 --> 00:09:13,548
Christ!

192
00:09:15,712 --> 00:09:18,040
Your mother's
last dying request

193
00:09:19,305 --> 00:09:21,110
on her deathbed

194
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:24,009
was that you didn't
run off with that

195
00:09:24,034 --> 00:09:25,892
slime, Frankie Adatto.

196
00:09:27,018 --> 00:09:29,901
You wouldn't give her that one
bit of satisfaction, would ya?

197
00:09:30,448 --> 00:09:32,502
You wouldn't
let her die in peace.

198
00:09:32,956 --> 00:09:34,385
I loved him.

199
00:09:36,259 --> 00:09:38,946
I was twenty,
I... I wanted more.

200
00:09:39,243 --> 00:09:40,235
More.

201
00:09:41,759 --> 00:09:43,212
More. More what?

202
00:09:43,548 --> 00:09:44,708
Jesus, Humpty.

203
00:09:44,834 --> 00:09:46,373
There's a world out there.

204
00:09:46,474 --> 00:09:48,084
This does not concern you.

205
00:09:48,505 --> 00:09:50,466
All I know is
you lost your head.

206
00:09:51,264 --> 00:09:53,693
Your head was in the clouds
over that gutter guinea

207
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:57,069
that flashy, cheap,
flashy little wop.

208
00:09:58,711 --> 00:10:01,485
You didn't think I knew
he carried a gun up here?

209
00:10:01,969 --> 00:10:02,664
Huh?

210
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:05,258
He'll know...
He'll know you came here.

211
00:10:05,414 --> 00:10:07,359
No. It's the last place he'll look.

212
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,750
He knows how you feel about me.

213
00:10:10,518 --> 00:10:11,377
Yeah.

214
00:10:12,057 --> 00:10:13,182
You mean he knows

215
00:10:13,307 --> 00:10:16,245
how much he hated me
for callin' it the way I saw it.

216
00:10:18,293 --> 00:10:19,333
Christ.

217
00:10:21,399 --> 00:10:23,594
I counted on you when she died.

218
00:10:24,727 --> 00:10:26,219
I was lost.

219
00:10:27,719 --> 00:10:29,875
You dumped me for that trash.

220
00:10:30,289 --> 00:10:32,469
That's why he wouldn't think
I'd come here.

221
00:10:33,586 --> 00:10:35,999
He knows that we haven't
exchanged words in five years

222
00:10:36,024 --> 00:10:38,055
'cause bad blood
between us ran too deep.

223
00:10:38,852 --> 00:10:40,368
He shows up here,
I'll kill him.

224
00:10:40,462 --> 00:10:43,461
Oh, God, don't say that.
I don't--I don't want trouble.

225
00:10:43,486 --> 00:10:44,157
All right.

226
00:10:44,194 --> 00:10:45,702
Okay, my nerves
are shot as it is

227
00:10:45,727 --> 00:10:47,636
-and you better calm down.
-All right.

228
00:10:49,371 --> 00:10:51,785
Just don't tell me what
I should or shouldn't do.

229
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:53,621
She's my daughter.

230
00:10:56,262 --> 00:10:58,136
Oh...

231
00:10:58,161 --> 00:10:58,925
Oh...Christ.

232
00:11:01,230 --> 00:11:02,637
You are a light, baby.

233
00:11:05,214 --> 00:11:06,839
You are a light in my life.

234
00:11:08,964 --> 00:11:10,519
Do you know
how much I missed you?

235
00:11:12,035 --> 00:11:12,847
Ha?

236
00:11:14,867 --> 00:11:16,820
Jesus! Suddenly, I'm starvin'.

237
00:11:18,273 --> 00:11:19,671
Clean the fish, Ginny.

238
00:11:20,375 --> 00:11:22,695
Yeah, yeah, I...I'll make
everybody stew.

239
00:11:22,961 --> 00:11:25,398
Yeah, no...cooking relaxes my nerves.

240
00:11:25,429 --> 00:11:27,671
Clean the fish?
I got a headache.

241
00:11:27,754 --> 00:11:29,355
Clean the fish, Ginny,

242
00:11:29,380 --> 00:11:31,761
two or three at least and
put paper down this time,

243
00:11:31,786 --> 00:11:34,223
last time you got
guts all over the floor.

244
00:11:36,950 --> 00:11:37,739
Hey,

245
00:11:38,278 --> 00:11:39,771
you remember Carolina?

246
00:11:40,099 --> 00:11:41,536
Remember I used to bake?

247
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:44,471
I used to make you those
chocolate chip cookies?

248
00:11:44,525 --> 00:11:45,307
Hm.

249
00:11:45,393 --> 00:11:46,960
And I'd put a little salt on it.

250
00:11:47,022 --> 00:11:47,937
Mm-hmm.

251
00:11:48,272 --> 00:11:50,764
You're late!
And you're in real trouble!

252
00:11:51,241 --> 00:11:53,585
You know you could
kill somebody starting fires!

253
00:11:53,652 --> 00:11:55,402
What kind of craziness is that?

254
00:11:55,598 --> 00:11:56,801
Hey, listen to me.

255
00:11:56,937 --> 00:11:58,171
You could hurt someone.

256
00:11:58,196 --> 00:12:00,703
W-Where'd you get this
idea to make fires?

257
00:12:02,556 --> 00:12:04,493
Jesus, Humpty, you sound
so happy tonight.

258
00:12:04,518 --> 00:12:06,079
What happened, your
number come in?

259
00:12:06,212 --> 00:12:07,822
Better than my number came in.

260
00:12:08,321 --> 00:12:09,766
My ship came home.

261
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:11,664
All right, well, have a good
night at the merry-go-round.

262
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:12,789
All right, you too, man.

263
00:12:13,726 --> 00:12:14,656
That's it.

264
00:12:14,921 --> 00:12:15,835
Leave it right there.

