♪ Though it consumes me ♪

779
00:36:24,622 --> 00:36:28,575
♪ Your Kiss of Fire ♪

780
00:36:30,847 --> 00:36:32,324
How's it coming?

781
00:36:34,824 --> 00:36:36,566
I know he has feelings for me.

782
00:36:36,902 --> 00:36:39,386
And I-I-I know it's not
just a summer thing.

783
00:36:39,571 --> 00:36:42,033
Oh, God, I hope I'm not
misreading it all.

784
00:36:42,244 --> 00:36:43,525
I mean, I try to...

785
00:36:43,697 --> 00:36:45,002
I try to push him

786
00:36:45,101 --> 00:36:47,210
without being one of
those pushy women.

787
00:36:48,187 --> 00:36:50,743
You know, I don't-don't
want my desperation to show.

788
00:36:51,052 --> 00:36:52,607
There's progress, but...

789
00:36:53,333 --> 00:36:54,685
it's slow.

790
00:36:55,167 --> 00:36:56,495
You know?

791
00:36:57,513 --> 00:36:58,982
As the summer ends and it...

792
00:36:59,208 --> 00:37:01,153
it fizzles out and I'm
left at square one.

793
00:37:01,178 --> 00:37:02,521
I don't know what I'll do.

794
00:37:02,577 --> 00:37:04,561
Well, you'll survive
like we all do.

795
00:37:04,695 --> 00:37:07,178
No. No, I'm not a strong person.

796
00:37:07,254 --> 00:37:09,207
I wouldn't have survived my
breakdown if it wasn't for Humpty.

797
00:37:09,241 --> 00:37:12,170
Now I'm feeling claustrophobic,
my headaches are back,

798
00:37:12,210 --> 00:37:13,796
You just have to be realistic

799
00:37:13,821 --> 00:37:15,929
in case things
don't go your way.

800
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:18,452
There is nothing realistic
about a Chinese garden

801
00:37:18,515 --> 00:37:20,624
in the middle of
Staten Island, but...

802
00:37:21,152 --> 00:37:24,253
but it's-it's-it's where
I wanna be with him.

803
00:37:24,699 --> 00:37:26,113
How's Richie doing?

804
00:37:26,746 --> 00:37:27,746
Richie?

805
00:37:28,496 --> 00:37:30,066
Oh, I never know
what's on his mind.

806
00:37:30,105 --> 00:37:34,582
♪ I touch your lips and all
at once the sparks go flying ♪

807
00:37:34,674 --> 00:37:39,003
♪ Those devil lips that know
so well the art of lying ♪

808
00:37:39,139 --> 00:37:43,600
♪ And though I see the danger,
still the flame grows higher ♪

809
00:37:43,638 --> 00:37:48,208
♪ I know I must surrender
to your kiss of fire ♪

810
00:37:48,281 --> 00:37:52,406
♪ Just like a torch, you set
the soul within me burning ♪

811
00:37:52,630 --> 00:37:56,958
♪ I must go on, I'm on this
road of no returning ♪

812
00:37:57,104 --> 00:38:00,439
♪ And though it burns me and
it turns me into ashes ♪

813
00:38:00,472 --> 00:38:03,112
I love your hair like this,
you look ten years younger.

814
00:38:03,152 --> 00:38:04,387
-You think?
-Uh-huh.

815
00:38:04,449 --> 00:38:06,684
Oof, I wish I had
your kind of hair.

816
00:38:06,723 --> 00:38:08,495
-Hey!
-The rainy weather kills me.

817
00:38:08,521 --> 00:38:09,445
Ginny!

818
00:38:10,328 --> 00:38:11,445
Ah, oh.

819
00:38:11,758 --> 00:38:13,258
-Oh, hi, hi.
-Hi.

820
00:38:13,375 --> 00:38:14,196
Hi.

821
00:38:14,430 --> 00:38:15,946
Um, this is Mickey.

822
00:38:16,274 --> 00:38:17,110
Hello.

823
00:38:17,281 --> 00:38:20,064
In case you never noticed,
he's the lifeguard on Bay 7.

824
00:38:20,089 --> 00:38:20,728
Oh.

825
00:38:20,806 --> 00:38:23,424
This is my husband's
daughter, Carolina.

826
00:38:23,588 --> 00:38:25,228
I swim at Bay 7 sometimes.

827
00:38:25,291 --> 00:38:26,892
-You do?
-Mm-hmm.

828
00:38:28,244 --> 00:38:29,783
We have to go.

829
00:38:30,752 --> 00:38:33,025
Just don't drown on
Bay 7 or they'll fire me.

830
00:38:34,936 --> 00:38:36,490
W-We should get going.

831
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:37,404
Okay.

832
00:38:37,506 --> 00:38:39,287
-Nice to meet you.
-You too.

833
00:38:41,248 --> 00:38:42,279
Cute.

834
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:43,853
Do you like my hair?

835
00:38:43,900 --> 00:38:45,111
Hm? Oh.

836
00:38:45,259 --> 00:38:47,689
Yes, it's...lovely.
Beautiful.

837
00:38:47,830 --> 00:38:50,924
♪ Your kiss of fire ♪

838
00:38:55,684 --> 00:38:58,606
Hey, I saw your daughter last
night, she was with a soldier.

839
00:38:58,669 --> 00:39:02,171
Ah, Jesus Christ, you put a uniform
on a guy, they lose their heads.

840
00:39:02,281 --> 00:39:03,093
It's true.

841
00:39:03,242 --> 00:39:06,140
I saw her with a sailor.
She's a very patriotic girl.

842
00:39:06,528 --> 00:39:08,286
Yeah, well, she's pretty, Humpty,

843
00:39:08,379 --> 00:39:09,794
you gotta expect some
trouble, you know.

844
00:39:09,819 --> 00:39:11,622
-Yeah, that's right.
-Her mother was pretty.

845
00:39:11,665 --> 00:39:12,766
And a saint.

846
00:39:13,303 --> 00:39:16,430
This girl's got a high IQ.
Her mother saw the number.

847
00:39:16,485 --> 00:39:16,993
Hm.

848
00:39:17,054 --> 00:39:19,007
I play the IQ number,
but it never comes in.

849
00:39:19,032 --> 00:39:21,242
No, I'm sure she can handle
herself, she's been married.

850
00:39:21,275 --> 00:39:22,565
Yeah, and knows the score.

851
00:39:22,619 --> 00:39:24,291
Yeah, he's right, you know,
once a woman's divorced,

852
00:39:24,316 --> 00:39:25,634
come on, she's
fair game, you know.

853
00:39:25,659 --> 00:39:26,822
-That's right.
-I'm glad I got boys, though.

854
00:39:26,847 --> 00:39:28,584
She's going to night school.

855
00:39:28,609 --> 00:39:30,123
She's gonna be an
English teacher

856
00:39:30,148 --> 00:39:32,412
Yeah, right, if some soldier
doesn't knock her up first.

857
00:39:32,469 --> 00:39:33,438
What the hell...?

858
00:39:33,789 --> 00:39:35,000
Come on, just kiddin'!

859
00:39:35,285 --> 00:39:36,293
Look how red he got.

860
00:39:36,886 --> 00:39:38,597
What kinda thing is that to say?

861
00:39:38,623 --> 00:39:40,684
She don't look like any English
teacher I had in school.

862
00:39:40,709 --> 00:39:42,424
Yeah, yeah, what
school did you go to?

863
00:39:42,449 --> 00:39:43,760
You didn't go to
school, you idiot.

864
00:39:43,785 --> 00:39:44,924
I went to the School
of Hard Knocks.

865
00:39:44,949 --> 00:39:45,815
Ah.

866
00:39:47,198 --> 00:39:48,151
Hi!

867
00:39:49,197 --> 00:39:50,095
Hey!

868
00:39:50,581 --> 00:39:52,627
-Remember me?
-Of course.

869
00:39:52,664 --> 00:39:54,202
We met outside the movie
theater the other night.

870
00:39:54,290 --> 00:39:56,336
-Yes!
-Oh. Gosh.

871
00:39:56,457 --> 00:39:57,676
Yes, with Ginny.

872
00:39:58,332 --> 00:40:00,700
You said you
sometimes use Bay 7.

873
00:40:01,464 --> 00:40:03,206
Yes, you remember.

874
00:40:03,269 --> 00:40:04,925
I was hoping to get some tan.

875
00:40:05,479 --> 00:40:08,527
-It's gotten so overcast.
-Yeah, storm clouds.

876
00:40:09,558 --> 00:40:10,691
What is it?

877
00:40:11,400 --> 00:40:15,454
<i>Hamlet and Oedipus</i> by
Ernest Jones.

878
00:40:15,712 --> 00:40:17,314
My goodness, that sounds deep.

879
00:40:17,837 --> 00:40:20,564
It's not that deep when you're
familiar with the total picture.

880
00:40:20,837 --> 00:40:22,283
What total picture is that?

881
00:40:23,019 --> 00:40:24,730
Well, Hamlet of course.

882
00:40:25,504 --> 00:40:27,457
I haven't read Hamlet
since high school.

883
00:40:28,012 --> 00:40:29,473
But you've seen it performed?

884
00:40:29,606 --> 00:40:31,770
Once, and not very well.

885
00:40:31,895 --> 00:40:34,887
I love the theater but
I haven't seen that many shows.

886
00:40:35,262 --> 00:40:37,153
I-Ignorance is no sin.

887
00:40:37,225 --> 00:40:39,374
It just means your experience
hasn't brought into contact

888
00:40:39,436 --> 00:40:40,827
-with certain things.
-Hm.

889
00:40:41,358 --> 00:40:44,343
-Did you finish school?
-No, I got sidetracked.

890
00:40:44,712 --> 00:40:47,439
Yeah, me too.
Uncle Sam.

891
00:40:47,842 --> 00:40:49,092
What's your story?

892
00:40:50,061 --> 00:40:51,928
I got married too quickly.

893
00:40:52,202 --> 00:40:53,553
But it's all over.

894
00:40:54,193 --> 00:40:55,076
Wow.

895
00:40:55,390 --> 00:40:57,218
Marriage is a big step, isn't it?

896
00:40:57,460 --> 00:40:58,812
-Hmm.
-Scary.

897
00:40:59,375 --> 00:41:00,679
What'd your husband do?

898
00:41:01,899 --> 00:41:04,297
Shouldn't you be looking
out for drowning people?

899
00:41:04,726 --> 00:41:08,195
No one ever drowns here.
But I should, yes.

900
00:41:08,327 --> 00:41:09,241
Listen,

901
00:41:09,585 --> 00:41:11,400
I'm actually through
with this book, so

902
00:41:11,439 --> 00:41:13,580
if you want, you can borrow it
and then when you're finished,

903
00:41:13,605 --> 00:41:15,126
then we could
discuss it more fully.

904
00:41:15,197 --> 00:41:16,666
-Really?
-Yeah.

905
00:41:16,921 --> 00:41:18,100
I'd like that.

906
00:41:19,411 --> 00:41:24,083
♪ Till I waltz again with you ♪

907
00:41:24,810 --> 00:41:29,966
♪ Let no other hold your charms ♪

908
00:41:30,357 --> 00:41:34,708
♪ If my dreams
should all come true ♪

909
00:41:35,497 --> 00:41:40,474
♪ You'll be waiting for my arms ♪

910
00:41:42,787 --> 00:41:45,545
You know who I ran into
yesterday at the beach?

911
00:41:45,732 --> 00:41:47,131
The lifeguard, Mickey.

912
00:41:47,232 --> 00:41:48,959
-You did?
-Yeah.

913
00:41:49,217 --> 00:41:51,451
I was leaving and I noticed
him, so I said hello.

914
00:41:51,476 --> 00:41:54,576
He was sitting up there reading and
he dropped down and we talked.

915
00:41:55,201 --> 00:41:56,404
He was very nice.

916
00:41:57,396 --> 00:41:58,170
Yeah?

917
00:41:58,779 --> 00:42:00,209
And he's well-educated.

918
00:42:00,412 --> 00:42:02,826
He's studying at college
to write plays.

919
00:42:03,917 --> 00:42:04,771
Uh-huh.

920
00:42:04,872 --> 00:42:06,920
I thought that would interest
you since you acted.

921
00:42:07,357 --> 00:42:10,451
And he had a book about Hamlet,
a psychological study.

922
00:42:11,381 --> 00:42:12,154
Uh-huh.

923
00:42:12,661 --> 00:42:14,262
I hadn't read Hamlet for years

924
00:42:14,287 --> 00:42:17,091
and he tried not to
make me feel so dumb.

925
00:42:17,867 --> 00:42:18,961
He was sweet.

926
00:42:20,250 --> 00:42:23,047
-How long'd you chat?
-Five minutes.

927
00:42:23,110 --> 00:42:25,423
I had to go home and shower
and dress for a date--

928
00:42:25,493 --> 00:42:28,337
a nice guy from night school,
took me to the movies.

929
00:42:28,431 --> 00:42:30,337
Not that I'd like
to see him again.

930
00:42:31,794 --> 00:42:34,457
That's...that's all you
talked about with Mickey?

931
00:42:34,489 --> 00:42:35,419
Yeah.

932
00:42:36,294 --> 00:42:37,255
Actually...

933
00:42:38,442 --> 00:42:40,075
I kind of found him attractive.

934
00:42:41,700 --> 00:42:42,786
Did you?

935
00:42:43,059 --> 00:42:44,973
Uh, I'm probably
reading into it, but

936
00:42:45,475 --> 00:42:47,241
I think he kind of liked me.

937
00:42:47,717 --> 00:42:50,303
He said I could borrow his book
and we could talk about it.

938
00:42:52,060 --> 00:42:54,037
That flounder was great.

939
00:42:54,506 --> 00:42:57,943
You know, that's the beauty of being
able to catch yourself a fresh.

940
00:42:58,330 --> 00:43:01,424
It's not just the money,
it's the flavor.

941
00:43:02,468 --> 00:43:04,358
-Carolina.
-Uh-huh?

942
00:43:04,483 --> 00:43:08,577
Carney and Ryan and Leo
think you're a knockout.

943
00:43:09,577 --> 00:43:12,952
Yeah, they kid me about
seeing you with that soldier.

944
00:43:13,017 --> 00:43:14,141
-Oh, Rusty Ford.
-Mm-hmm.

945
00:43:14,166 --> 00:43:16,407
No, he's a real hero,
he fought in Okinawa.

946
00:43:16,642 --> 00:43:18,587
Hey, what am I, the hired help?

947
00:43:19,175 --> 00:43:21,222
You ever think of
clearing you own stuff?

948
00:43:21,582 --> 00:43:24,418
I'm sorry, every time I try,
you send me back down.

949
00:43:24,521 --> 00:43:27,152
That's because we can't afford
to have any more dishes broken

950
00:43:27,177 --> 00:43:30,106
but you could overrule
me and just...be careful.

951
00:43:30,131 --> 00:43:31,966
Oh, of course, no,
I'm happy to help.

952
00:43:32,263 --> 00:43:34,564
I'd do the dishes but
I just did my nails.

953
00:43:34,634 --> 00:43:36,408
Well, I don't feel like
doing them tonight.

954
00:43:36,642 --> 00:43:38,236
She just did her nails.

955
00:43:38,822 --> 00:43:40,423
When you're married
to a man who got rich

956
00:43:40,448 --> 00:43:41,626
putting people's
feet in cement,

957
00:43:41,657 --> 00:43:43,408
you probably never
had to do a dish.

958
00:43:43,479 --> 00:43:44,479
I'll do it.

959
00:43:45,028 --> 00:43:46,687
-I'll do it.
-I got it.

960
00:43:47,671 --> 00:43:49,382
"Starring as a waitress."

961
00:43:49,945 --> 00:43:51,390
Something's eatin' her.

962
00:43:51,634 --> 00:43:54,173
It's my fault. I should insist
on doing more around here.

963
00:43:54,198 --> 00:43:56,564
-Well, pfff...
-No, she's right, I'm not used to it.

964
00:43:56,589 --> 00:43:58,354
I'm between work
and studying, I...

965
00:43:58,393 --> 00:44:01,128
Well, listen...just get
home early, that's all.

966
00:44:02,646 --> 00:44:04,911
Hey, was everything okay?

967
00:44:05,521 --> 00:44:06,333
Yeah.

968
00:44:07,193 --> 00:44:07,966
Why?

969
00:44:08,271 --> 00:44:10,208
You seemed a little distracted.

970
00:44:12,880 --> 00:44:15,443
Carolina told me you ran
into her at the beach.

971
00:44:16,565 --> 00:44:17,987
Ran into her?

972
00:44:18,081 --> 00:44:19,870
I nearly hit her in the
head with my book.

973
00:44:20,854 --> 00:44:22,370
She said you lent it to her.

974
00:44:22,596 --> 00:44:24,189
Yeah, she was interested.

975
00:44:24,292 --> 00:44:27,206
You shouldn't read out there.
People trust you with their lives.

976
00:44:27,231 --> 00:44:28,741
So, what'd you
talk to her about?

977
00:44:28,913 --> 00:44:31,178
Nothing. Uh, my book--Hamlet.

978
00:44:31,225 --> 00:44:32,795
She said she quit
school to get married.

979
00:44:32,873 --> 00:44:33,975
To a gangster.

980
00:44:34,997 --> 00:44:37,474
Really? How interesting.

981
00:44:37,591 --> 00:44:38,857
You find that interesting?

982
00:44:38,911 --> 00:44:41,021
They're after her.
They want to kill her.

983
00:44:41,181 --> 00:44:42,165
You better be careful.

984
00:44:42,219 --> 00:44:44,517
I get the creeps living in that
apartment. I wish she'd move on.

985
00:44:44,704 --> 00:44:47,071
-She never mentioned it.
-Well, she wouldn't.

986
00:44:47,096 --> 00:44:49,610
She's embarrassed by how
she screwed up her life.

987
00:44:50,082 --> 00:44:51,637
They're gonna find her
and kill her?

988
00:44:51,662 --> 00:44:53,145
Y-You must be exaggerating.

989
00:44:53,832 --> 00:44:55,129
It's a long story.

990
00:44:55,395 --> 00:44:57,793
She's a canary. She sings.

991
00:44:58,086 --> 00:45:01,289
That's terrible.
She's young, she's pretty.

992
00:45:01,461 --> 00:45:02,938
She should go
where she's safe.

993
00:45:03,141 --> 00:45:05,000
I asked you the other
day if she was pretty

994
00:45:05,133 --> 00:45:06,930
and you said, "Okay".

995
00:45:06,992 --> 00:45:08,930
Was so quick, I didn't
really get a good look.

996
00:45:09,602 --> 00:45:11,953
But at the beach she
had on a bathing suit.

997
00:45:12,189 --> 00:45:13,932
Yeah, well, sort of.

998
00:45:14,369 --> 00:45:15,971
You didn't get any
ideas, did you?

999
00:45:16,186 --> 00:45:18,335
-What kind of ideas?
-What do you think?

1000
00:45:18,360 --> 00:45:20,827
Hey, give me a break.
What are you doing?

1001
00:45:20,852 --> 00:45:23,565
She's not for you.
She's hiding out here.

1002
00:45:23,745 --> 00:45:25,659
Her life’s all topsy-turvy.

1003
00:45:25,854 --> 00:45:27,659
I was just chatting with her.

1004
00:45:27,705 --> 00:45:30,221
Well, I hope you didn't
say anything about us.

1005
00:45:30,388 --> 00:45:31,778
You know, she'll tell her father.

1006
00:45:31,849 --> 00:45:33,614
-That's what canaries do.
-Of course, I'm gonna do that.

1007
00:45:33,708 --> 00:45:34,482
They sing.

1008
00:45:34,521 --> 00:45:35,739
What do you think I'm a dope?

1009
00:45:35,786 --> 00:45:37,482
L-Let's get off this topic.

1010
00:45:37,661 --> 00:45:39,521
Hey, you were in my
dream last night.

1011
00:45:40,083 --> 00:45:40,950
Yeah?

1012
00:45:41,669 --> 00:45:44,263
What, I'm supposed to be
flattered you dream of me?

1013
00:45:45,232 --> 00:45:46,857
I rescued you in the dream.

1014
00:45:49,099 --> 00:45:50,185
Rescue me?

1015
00:45:51,474 --> 00:45:52,724
What can I tell you?

1016
00:45:52,787 --> 00:45:54,708
I'm not gonna tell Ginny
my real feelings.

1017
00:45:54,763 --> 00:45:55,943
How could I?

1018
00:45:56,248 --> 00:45:58,428
But I was taken with Carolina.

1019
00:45:58,694 --> 00:46:00,436
Something hit me right off.

1020
00:46:00,643 --> 00:46:03,581
The more I talked with her,
the more I was intrigued by her.

1021
00:46:03,979 --> 00:46:06,510
I felt a buzz all day
after our encounter.

1022
00:46:07,331 --> 00:46:09,268
I'd like to see her
again but obviously

1023
00:46:09,293 --> 00:46:11,581
I can't be honest with
Ginny about that.

1024
00:46:12,159 --> 00:46:14,363
The last thing I wanna
do is hurt Ginny

1025
00:46:14,399 --> 00:46:16,102
or wreck a good thing.

1026
00:46:16,735 --> 00:46:18,837
