I-I do, she told me her story.
It's chilling.

1524
01:06:31,985 --> 01:06:33,774
Would you like to spend
more time with her?

1525
01:06:34,809 --> 01:06:36,231
Why do you say that?

1526
01:06:36,481 --> 01:06:38,114
Well, that's the
impression she got.

1527
01:06:38,215 --> 01:06:41,129
Look, this is supposed to be
your birthday celebration

1528
01:06:41,166 --> 01:06:43,580
and it's turning into
the third degree.

1529
01:06:43,924 --> 01:06:45,486
Can't you see I'm jealous?

1530
01:06:46,244 --> 01:06:48,596
Nothing's happened
to be jealous of.

1531
01:06:48,682 --> 01:06:51,798
I was hoping...
we might have a future together.

1532
01:06:52,777 --> 01:06:54,395
Yes, I know, I...

1533
01:06:54,505 --> 01:06:57,317
I told you we'd talk about
it when the time comes.

1534
01:06:57,585 --> 01:06:59,233
If you told her she
had a beautiful face,

1535
01:06:59,266 --> 01:07:01,234
what the hell is-is she
supposed to think?

1536
01:07:01,304 --> 01:07:02,796
What the hell am I
supposed to think?

1537
01:07:02,846 --> 01:07:05,925
Hey, we were sitting in
the car on a rainy day--

1538
01:07:05,987 --> 01:07:08,330
that light would've
looked soft on any woman.

1539
01:07:08,355 --> 01:07:11,487
You know what, this conversation
is-is starting to take a crazy turn.

1540
01:07:11,681 --> 01:07:13,985
I've become consumed
with jealousy!

1541
01:07:15,794 --> 01:07:17,388
Can we start the day over?

1542
01:07:18,701 --> 01:07:20,779
I really hope you like
your birthday present.

1543
01:07:21,169 --> 01:07:22,739
O'Neill was a great one.

1544
01:07:23,630 --> 01:07:25,435
Great and terrifying.

1545
01:07:27,692 --> 01:07:29,982
Of course I felt terrible.

1546
01:07:30,089 --> 01:07:31,730
I needed to talk
the situation over

1547
01:07:31,840 --> 01:07:34,278
with someone a lot
sharper than me.

1548
01:07:34,544 --> 01:07:36,661
I called my friend Jake Jacoby

1549
01:07:36,704 --> 01:07:38,883
who's a graduate
student at city college

1550
01:07:38,908 --> 01:07:40,595
in the philosophy department.

1551
01:07:40,729 --> 01:07:42,627
It doesn't make sense because

1552
01:07:42,808 --> 01:07:46,316
you're not dealing with sense,
you're dealing with feelings.

1553
01:07:47,057 --> 01:07:48,705
Feelings, my friend.

1554
01:07:48,799 --> 01:07:50,416
It's a whole different ballgame.

1555
01:07:50,737 --> 01:07:54,018
The whole thing
is so irrational.

1556
01:07:54,143 --> 01:07:56,682
I've been seeing this
married woman all summer.

1557
01:07:56,846 --> 01:07:58,768
And she has these fantasies of

1558
01:07:58,899 --> 01:08:01,384
leaving her husband
and going away with me.

1559
01:08:01,688 --> 01:08:04,977
Her fondest wish would be
to divorce him and marry me.

1560
01:08:06,040 --> 01:08:08,540
And at times I see it

1561
01:08:08,681 --> 01:08:10,142
and at times I don't.

1562
01:08:11,484 --> 01:08:14,265
She's older than me
and I like that.

1563
01:08:15,210 --> 01:08:17,570
Somehow it fits into
the romantic narrative of

1564
01:08:17,608 --> 01:08:19,124
the writer's life.

1565
01:08:21,793 --> 01:08:23,809
But she's more than that.

1566
01:08:24,137 --> 01:08:26,989
So-So-So why am I hesitant?

1567
01:08:27,133 --> 01:08:28,265
One minute I'm not sure,

1568
01:08:28,313 --> 01:08:30,235
the next I'm ready to
take charge of her life--

1569
01:08:30,289 --> 01:08:31,696
to rescue her.

1570
01:08:32,356 --> 01:08:34,825
Can-Can this Carolina
be relied on?

1571
01:08:34,880 --> 01:08:37,583
After all, she-she did
run away with gangsters

1572
01:08:37,794 --> 01:08:39,598
because she was a thrillseeker.

1573
01:08:39,693 --> 01:08:41,935
Uh... you know...

1574
01:08:42,045 --> 01:08:44,146
did-did-did she learn her lesson?

1575
01:08:45,583 --> 01:08:47,935
She may give you
a period of bliss

1576
01:08:48,106 --> 01:08:49,770
but will it sustain?

1577
01:08:50,371 --> 01:08:52,566
Will this other one be

1578
01:08:52,823 --> 01:08:54,934
a more solid fit for you?

1579
01:08:55,495 --> 01:08:58,558
When I hear you say it,
I think,

1580
01:08:58,823 --> 01:09:00,417
yes, she would.

1581
01:09:01,507 --> 01:09:04,664
And-And Ginny's counting
on me, she's drowning.

1582
01:09:04,834 --> 01:09:08,131
Yeah, she'd be eternally
grateful for a lifeline.

1583
01:09:09,128 --> 01:09:13,612
Af-After all, you know, a love
so intense as hers is for you

1584
01:09:13,683 --> 01:09:16,472
is a rare gift to have
bestowed on a man.

1585
01:09:22,150 --> 01:09:24,017
It's amazing how
lucid things become

1586
01:09:24,095 --> 01:09:26,118
when you get an
outside perspective.

1587
01:09:26,653 --> 01:09:30,786
At that moment, a fog lifted
and my choice was obvious.

1588
01:09:31,065 --> 01:09:32,987
Carolina was a lovely daydream

1589
01:09:33,026 --> 01:09:36,589
but reality, with all its pros
and cons, belonged to Ginny.

1590
01:09:37,187 --> 01:09:40,234
All my silly schemes to
pursue Carolina seemed crazy

1591
01:09:40,259 --> 01:09:43,805
and I made the decision to never
entertain that pipe dream again.

1592
01:09:45,203 --> 01:09:48,570
But as Jake said, the heart
has its own hieroglyphics.

1593
01:09:49,399 --> 01:09:50,649
Maybe he was right.

1594
01:09:51,352 --> 01:09:52,399
Hi!

1595
01:09:53,276 --> 01:09:54,932
I came to tell you something.

1596
01:09:55,833 --> 01:09:56,763
Oh, yeah?

1597
01:09:56,926 --> 01:09:58,254
I thought of you yesterday.

1598
01:09:58,324 --> 01:10:00,051
I know you mentioned
that you love pizza.

1599
01:10:00,207 --> 01:10:02,261
And somebody said he knew the
greatest pizza place in Brooklyn.

1600
01:10:02,308 --> 01:10:04,051
And he took me there
and he was right.

1601
01:10:04,176 --> 01:10:05,621
And I thought you'd
wanna know about it.

1602
01:10:05,998 --> 01:10:07,349
Your boyfriend took you?

1603
01:10:07,607 --> 01:10:09,888
It's called Capri, it's a few
blocks from the boardwalk

1604
01:10:09,913 --> 01:10:11,099
not far from here.

1605
01:10:11,334 --> 01:10:12,685
Will you let me take you there?

1606
01:10:13,292 --> 01:10:15,128
I'm kinda busy
with school all week.

1607
01:10:16,651 --> 01:10:17,995
Is Friday night good?

1608
01:10:20,628 --> 01:10:21,909
Friday, I can do.

1609
01:10:22,838 --> 01:10:24,120
And he's not my boyfriend.

1610
01:10:25,137 --> 01:10:29,559
♪ I touch your lips and all
at once the sparks go flying ♪

1611
01:10:29,720 --> 01:10:33,915
♪ Those devil lips that know
so well the art of lying ♪

1612
01:10:34,290 --> 01:10:38,610
♪ And though I see the danger,
still the flame grows higher ♪

1613
01:10:38,743 --> 01:10:43,016
♪ I know I must surrender
to your kiss of fire ♪

1614
01:10:43,073 --> 01:10:46,075
♪ Just like a torch, you set
the soul within me burning ♪

1615
01:10:46,106 --> 01:10:48,018
-Good morning, ma'am.
-Morning.

1616
01:10:48,771 --> 01:10:50,536
-Do you still have it?
-Yes, I do.

1617
01:10:53,662 --> 01:10:54,881
I've got the money.

1618
01:10:55,912 --> 01:10:57,225
-Here.
-Great.

1619
01:11:01,244 --> 01:11:02,228
Wonderful.

1620
01:11:03,455 --> 01:11:05,416
Can you take it in the back
and engrave it?

1621
01:11:05,494 --> 01:11:07,424
Of course, what do
you want it to say?

1622
01:11:07,822 --> 01:11:10,322
♪ You're all that I desire ♪

1623
01:11:10,463 --> 01:11:14,682
♪ Since first I kissed you
my heart was yours completely ♪

1624
01:11:15,246 --> 01:11:16,683
♪ If I'm a slave ♪
-Hi.

1625
01:11:16,737 --> 01:11:19,714
♪ Then it's a slave I want to be ♪

1626
01:11:19,940 --> 01:11:21,714
♪ Don't pity me ♪

1627
01:11:22,205 --> 01:11:25,839
♪ Don't pity me ♪

1628
01:11:26,945 --> 01:11:30,703
♪ Give me your lips,
the lips you only let me borrow ♪

1629
01:11:31,258 --> 01:11:35,500
♪ Love me tonight and let
the devil take tomorrow ♪

1630
01:11:35,847 --> 01:11:40,003
♪ I know that I must have your
kiss although it dooms me ♪

1631
01:11:40,135 --> 01:11:41,846
♪ Though it consumes me ♪

1632
01:11:41,963 --> 01:11:46,472
♪ Your kiss of fire ♪

1633
01:11:53,982 --> 01:11:58,303
♪ Since first I kissed you
my heart was yours completely ♪

1634
01:12:00,926 --> 01:12:03,410
I'm glad we could steal
these few minutes.

1635
01:12:04,230 --> 01:12:06,574
No one will see us this end
of the boardwalk, it's

1636
01:12:06,746 --> 01:12:08,176
it's so private.

1637
01:12:08,981 --> 01:12:10,285
I wanted to talk to you.

1638
01:12:10,363 --> 01:12:13,039
But first, I want to talk to you.

1639
01:12:14,032 --> 01:12:14,782
Okay.

1640
01:12:15,305 --> 01:12:16,914
Don't look so worried.

1641
01:12:17,141 --> 01:12:18,774
Mine is a nice thing.

1642
01:12:19,852 --> 01:12:20,641
What?

1643
01:12:24,001 --> 01:12:25,102
Did you miss me?

1644
01:12:25,610 --> 01:12:28,274
Well, you've been so
busy with your son--

1645
01:12:28,321 --> 01:12:30,000
That's not what I asked you.

1646
01:12:30,079 --> 01:12:31,704
-Did you miss me?
-Jesus, Ginny.

1647
01:12:31,758 --> 01:12:33,219
-Why are you always so evasive?
-Take it easy.

1648
01:12:33,313 --> 01:12:35,696
You never wanna talk
about anything.

1649
01:12:36,986 --> 01:12:39,970
Okay, look, I don't want
to get off to a bad start.

1650
01:12:41,563 --> 01:12:43,750
Remember last week
it was my birthday?

1651
01:12:44,500 --> 01:12:46,821
-Yes.
-Well, today is yours.

1652
01:12:47,784 --> 01:12:48,836
How'd you know?

1653
01:12:49,469 --> 01:12:50,836
You mentioned it.

1654
01:12:51,628 --> 01:12:53,550
Remember we're both Leos?

1655
01:12:54,080 --> 01:12:57,159
I mentioned it ages ago.
What a memory.

1656
01:12:58,541 --> 01:12:59,564
What is that?

1657
01:13:00,010 --> 01:13:01,245
I got you a present.

1658
01:13:01,432 --> 01:13:03,346
-No.
-Here.

1659
01:13:13,304 --> 01:13:14,530
Oh, God.

1660
01:13:14,765 --> 01:13:17,257
You-You...
You can't do that.

1661
01:13:17,976 --> 01:13:20,420
-Why not?
-I-It's not right.

1662
01:13:20,984 --> 01:13:22,172
You got me a gift.

1663
01:13:22,234 --> 01:13:25,242
I know, but...
what the hell, I got you a book.

1664
01:13:25,384 --> 01:13:28,173
This is... i-i-it's-
it's much too expensive.

1665
01:13:28,235 --> 01:13:29,352
I can't accept this.

1666
01:13:29,398 --> 01:13:30,649
How would you know
it's so expensive?

1667
01:13:30,674 --> 01:13:32,274
I've inquired about this watch.

1668
01:13:32,299 --> 01:13:34,133
-I was with you.
-Ginny.

1669
01:13:34,508 --> 01:13:37,929
Okay. This is a $500 watch.

1670
01:13:38,266 --> 01:13:39,789
But you always
wanted this watch.

1671
01:13:39,814 --> 01:13:41,859
Yes, but it's much
too extravagant.

1672
01:13:41,884 --> 01:13:43,890
-You can't afford this.
-That's my business.

1673
01:13:44,004 --> 01:13:46,684
And even if you could, it's
much too extravagant, given...

1674
01:13:46,754 --> 01:13:48,231
Given what?
Given-Given what?

1675
01:13:48,262 --> 01:13:49,723
It's too much to spend on me.

1676
01:13:49,785 --> 01:13:51,590
You shouldn't be
getting me jewelry.

1677
01:13:52,192 --> 01:13:54,715
Why not?
Is it too meaningful?

1678
01:13:55,364 --> 01:13:57,700
Oh, Christ. You inscribed it.

1679
01:13:57,926 --> 01:13:58,981
Yeah, read it.

1680
01:14:01,871 --> 01:14:02,770
Look...

1681
01:14:04,483 --> 01:14:06,139
We have to have a talk.

1682
01:14:06,662 --> 01:14:08,311
I thought you'd be excited.

1683
01:14:08,690 --> 01:14:10,790
It's too much and I can't
accept this watch.

1684
01:14:10,815 --> 01:14:12,096
Stop saying that!

1685
01:14:12,121 --> 01:14:14,026
You can't be buying
me a $500 watch.

1686
01:14:14,202 --> 01:14:15,874
Look, why?

1687
01:14:16,022 --> 01:14:18,491
Y-You're always saying
what a beautiful, perfect

1688
01:14:18,530 --> 01:14:20,600
summer it's been, and-and...

1689
01:14:21,587 --> 01:14:24,181
It's not right given
the circumstances.

1690
01:14:24,322 --> 01:14:25,572
What circumstances?

1691
01:14:25,658 --> 01:14:26,697
What are the goddamn
circumstances?

1692
01:14:26,722 --> 01:14:29,026
That you're ready
to get very serious

1693
01:14:29,070 --> 01:14:30,992
and I'm just not ready.

1694
01:14:31,211 --> 01:14:32,617
Something's happened.

1695
01:14:32,734 --> 01:14:34,156
Something's happened,
everything was--

1696
01:14:34,218 --> 01:14:36,538
Everything was going so smoothly.
Something's gone wrong.

1697
01:14:36,571 --> 01:14:38,406
I don't wanna disappoint you.

1698
01:14:38,906 --> 01:14:41,054
Look, you-you said you love me.

1699
01:14:41,364 --> 01:14:42,903
Were you insincere?

1700
01:14:44,598 --> 01:14:46,965
It's not that I wasn't trying.

1701
01:14:47,418 --> 01:14:49,824
Of course if you have to try.
It's-It's not homework.

1702
01:14:49,871 --> 01:14:53,230
I'm not saying I don't have
real feelings for you.

1703
01:14:54,375 --> 01:14:55,656
Is it Carolina?

1704
01:14:56,297 --> 01:14:59,555
Jesus Christ, I hardly
know Carolina.

1705
01:14:59,637 --> 01:15:01,051
But you wanna get to know her.

1706
01:15:01,076 --> 01:15:03,074
And I should wait around
while you could try her out?

1707
01:15:03,099 --> 01:15:04,388
Hey, I didn't say that.

1708
01:15:04,638 --> 01:15:06,208
I didn't say that.
You're losing it.

1709
01:15:06,393 --> 01:15:08,369
You know what?
You don't want it?

1710
01:15:08,705 --> 01:15:11,510
Forget it. Huh?
Forget it!

1711
01:15:11,572 --> 01:15:12,494
-What the hell are you doing?
-Forget it!

1712
01:15:12,580 --> 01:15:13,565
Ginny!

1713
01:15:13,744 --> 01:15:16,080
-Are you crazy?
-Don't talk to me!

1714
01:15:17,813 --> 01:15:20,876
All right, you little punk, give me
back that money or I'll kill ya.

1715
01:15:21,081 --> 01:15:22,557
Hey, w-what's going on?

1716
01:15:22,631 --> 01:15:23,280
I didn't take his money!

1717
01:15:23,305 --> 01:15:25,702
Don't tell me, you little thief,
you're always stealing from me.

1718
01:15:25,810 --> 01:15:27,911
He took 400 bucks
out of my tin box.

1719
01:15:27,936 --> 01:15:29,341
I did not!

1720
01:15:29,416 --> 01:15:32,017
You know what? That's 400 bucks.
That's grand larceny.

1721
01:15:32,124 --> 01:15:33,858
You know, I ougta
bang it outta ya.

1722
01:15:33,960 --> 01:15:35,038
He didn't take it.

1723
01:15:35,132 --> 01:15:37,514
Don't-Don't be tellin'
me he didn't take it.

1724
01:15:37,600 --> 01:15:39,108
You know, you're always
stickin' up for him.

1725
01:15:39,177 --> 01:15:40,888
That's why he is
the way he is.

1726
01:15:40,913 --> 01:15:43,030
-Now you give me that money back.
-I took it.

1727
01:15:43,163 --> 01:15:44,405
Don't make up a story.

1728
01:15:44,436 --> 01:15:46,436
I took the money, not him.

1729
01:15:48,309 --> 01:15:49,340
You took it?

1730
01:15:49,871 --> 01:15:53,473
Yeah, I-I-I needed it to
pay for a psychiatrist for him.

1731
01:15:53,652 --> 01:15:54,574
What?!

1732
01:15:54,675 --> 01:15:56,847
That's right, they're-they're
a lot of money and

1733
01:15:56,895 --> 01:15:58,957
and he's been goin'
every few days. I...

1734
01:15:59,073 --> 01:16:00,808
I-I-I didn't wanna tell you.

1735
01:16:00,861 --> 01:16:05,440
Wait, y-y-you took my savings
to pay for a head doctor?

1736
01:16:05,502 --> 01:16:07,276
He needs help.

1737
01:16:07,307 --> 01:16:10,377
Yeah, you know what? I was saving
that money for Carolina's school.

1738
01:16:10,402 --> 01:16:13,217
Well, she'll just have to put
some of her dreams on hold.

1739
01:16:13,293 --> 01:16:14,699
I got a call
from his doctor

1740
01:16:14,724 --> 01:16:16,777
that he started a fire
in her waiting room.

1741
01:16:16,983 --> 01:16:19,014
Richie! Is that so?

1742
01:16:19,145 --> 01:16:20,731
I don't wanna go back there.

1743
01:16:20,783 --> 01:16:23,674
You know what? You steal. What
kind of example is that? Jesus.

1744
01:16:23,739 --> 01:16:25,622
Oh, God, I can't
handle this now.

1745
01:16:25,708 --> 01:16:27,364
Look, I-I-I'm late for work.

1746
01:16:27,473 --> 01:16:31,098
I am sick of waiting on tables
and kicking in my salary so that

1747
01:16:31,184 --> 01:16:34,012
you can put away your
extra money for Carolina.

1748
01:16:34,074 --> 01:16:37,058
Oh, God! Now my
head is pounding.

1749
01:16:37,183 --> 01:16:38,737
Well, take an aspirin.

1750
01:16:38,816 --> 01:16:40,590
I don't want an aspirin.

1751
01:16:40,690 --> 01:16:42,182
I want a Scotch!

1752
01:16:42,332 --> 01:16:44,215
Take an aspirin!

1753
01:16:46,152 --> 01:16:47,996
Jeez, so that's where
you've been hidin' it.

1754
01:16:48,183 --> 01:16:49,543
I knew you had a stash.

1755
01:16:49,611 --> 01:16:52,048
And when I begged you for
a shot, when I needed it

1756
01:16:52,079 --> 01:16:53,571
you wouldn't give me,
but when you need one, you--

1757
01:16:53,611 --> 01:16:54,602
You're not allowed.

1758
01:16:54,627 --> 01:16:55,673
I knew you had a bottle.

1759
01:16:55,698 --> 01:16:56,751
-I knew it.
-Hi!

1760
01:16:56,776 --> 01:16:58,876
I'm late, I'm such a scatterbrain.

1761
01:16:58,935 --> 01:17:01,029
I have a date
and I forgot my wallet.

1762
01:17:01,308 --> 01:17:03,433
Uh, I'm meeting Mickey
and I found

1763
01:17:03,620 --> 01:17:05,159
this great pizza place.

1764
01:17:05,242 --> 01:17:06,875
It's his birthday,
so I'm treating.

1765
01:17:06,914 --> 01:17:08,851
What, y-y-you're
going with Mickey?

1766
